<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="513" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1642,1885]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1642,1668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[332,559,1642,1669]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" pagination="445 - 470" refId="ref10667" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. res. (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 445 - 470. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[413,465,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
. Characteristic added here: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[878,1057,1642,1668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface of the pygophore with spot restricted to coarse area (
<figureCitation box="[549,648,1678,1704]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
— 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[677,910,1678,1705]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" pagination="445 - 470" refId="ref10667" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. res. (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 445 - 470. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[758,808,1678,1704]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">et al</emphasis>
. (2020))
</bibRefCitation>
. Inner wall with swollen area globose close to superior process of genital cup (
<figureCitation box="[524,614,1714,1740]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[250,1339,204,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[199,1389,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genital capsule in posterolateral view, swollen area on inner wall of the pygophore indicated by the arrow: A—Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
, black arrow). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[790,997,1714,1740]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Valvifers VIII with mediolateral crest slightly swollen (
<figureCitation box="[345,432,1750,1776]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[247,1354,212,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-25@14.[199,1389,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Female genital plates in oblique view, mediolateral crest swollen on valvifers VIII indicated by the arrow: A— Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911528/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
, black arrow).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
