<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="513" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1642,1885]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1822,1848]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Comments.</emphasis>
The swollen area on inner wall of the pygophore is the innermost one compared to other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[151,324,1857,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,1857,1884]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">H. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. See 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[458,576,1859,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[458,576,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">H. striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[583,646,1858,1884]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[583,646,1858,1884]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
comments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
